[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m711[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m   [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwStream* WINPR_RESTRICT s,[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m712[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m   [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUINT16* WINPR_RESTRICT pExpectedBlockType[0m[1;39m)[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m713[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m714[0m[39m:    [0m[39mUINT32 magic = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m715[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m716[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m717[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m718[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmessage[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m719[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m720[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpExpectedBlockType[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m721[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m722[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m*pExpectedBlockType != WBT_FRAME_END[0m[1;39m)[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m723[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m724[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mWLog_Print[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv->log, WLOG_ERROR, [0m[32m"message unexpected [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mwants WBT_FRAME_END [0m[32m([0m[32m0x%x[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, *pExpectedBlockType[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m725[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn FALSE;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m726[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m727[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m728[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT32[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, magic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* magic [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0xCACCACCA[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m729[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmagic != WF_MAGIC[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m730[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m731[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mWLog_Print[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv->log, WLOG_ERROR, [0m[32m"invalid magic number [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m0x%08"[0m[39m PRIX32 [0m[32m""[0m[39m, magic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m732[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn FALSE;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m733[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m734[0m[39m:    [0m[39m*[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m735[0m[39m:    [0m[39mreturn TRUE;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m736[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis of the Issue[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe evaluation report clearly shows that the previous patch attempt failed to [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolve the vulnerability. The crash still occurs, just at a different line number [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m727[0m[39m instead of [0m[1;36m734[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which is exactly [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m lines earlier - matching the number of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlines removed by the patch.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the code snippets, the root cause is an **arbitrary write [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability** in the WBT_METADATA processing logic:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Global variables** `metadataBlock` and `metadataData` are initialized at lines[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m142[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m179[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. In `rfx_process_message_frame_begin` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m674[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m680[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, if extra data is present [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the stream, it reads:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `blockOffset` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - attacker-controlled[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `metadataData` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - attacker-controlled  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Then modifies: `metadataBlock += blockOffset` - allowing arbitrary address [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalculation[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. In `rfx_process_message_metadata` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m734[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, it executes: [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`*[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData;`[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This writes attacker-controlled data to an attacker-controlled address[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why the Previous Patch Failed[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe previous patch removed lines [0m[1;36m674[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m680[0m[39m, which prevented reading `blockOffset` and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`metadataData` from the stream. However:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `metadataBlock` still retains its initial value: `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m&explicit_bzero` [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39maddress of a function, likely in read-only .text section[0m[1;39m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `metadataData` still retains its initial value: `[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m734[0m[39m **still executes**: `*[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData;`[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This attempts to write [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m to the address of `explicit_bzero`, causing a SEGV in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread-only memory[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe crash moved from line [0m[1;36m734[0m[39m to line [0m[1;36m727[0m[39m only because of line number shifts, but [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe actual crashing instruction at line [0m[1;36m734[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow [0m[1;36m727[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m still executes.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Evidence of Unused/Dangerous Code[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **No legitimate usage**: The encoder never writes WBT_METADATA blocks [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rfx_write_message_metadata` function exists[0m[1;39m)[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **No test coverage**: Test data contains no WBT_METADATA blocks[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **No documentation**: No comments or specification references explain the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata feature[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Design flaws**: [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Uses dangerous global variables instead of per-context fields[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Not thread-safe[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - State persists across context boundaries[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Missing stream validation[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Suspicious initialization**: `metadataBlock = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m&explicit_bzero` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuggests incomplete/abandoned development code[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Comprehensive Fix Strategy[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability requires complete removal of the WBT_METADATA feature. The fix [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmust eliminate all code paths that use the global metadata variables and process [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWBT_METADATA blocks.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Remove Global Variable Declarations[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File: `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.c`**[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRemove the global variable declarations:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m142[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m143[0m[39m: Remove `UINT64 metadataBlock = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m&explicit_bzero;` and the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblank line[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m179[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m180[0m[39m: Remove `UINT64 metadataData = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;` and the blank line[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Remove Metadata Reading from FRAME_BEGIN[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File: `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.c`**[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIn the `rfx_process_message_frame_begin` function [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m647[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m685[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Remove lines [0m[1;36m674[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m680[0m[39m: The conditional block that reads `blockOffset` and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`metadataData` from the stream and modifies `metadataBlock`[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis is the same removal as the previous patch, but it must be combined with the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mother removals to be effective.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Remove WBT_METADATA Processing Function[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File: `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.c`**[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRemove the entire `rfx_process_message_metadata` function [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m709[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m736[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Has no legitimate purpose[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Contains the vulnerable write at line [0m[1;36m734[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Is only called when processing WBT_METADATA blocks[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m: Remove WBT_METADATA Case from Switch Statement[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File: `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.c`**[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIn the `rfx_process_message` function, remove the WBT_METADATA case from the switch[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstatement [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1319[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1322[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcase WBT_METADATA:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ok = [0m[1;35mrfx_process_message_metadata[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext, message, subStream,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                     &context->expectedDataBlockType[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    break;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis prevents WBT_METADATA blocks from being processed. Any such blocks in input [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwill fall through to the `default` case, which logs an error and returns FALSE.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m: [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional but Recommended[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Remove WBT_METADATA Constant[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File: `libfreerdp/codec/rfx_constants.h`**[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOptionally remove line [0m[1;36m38[0m[39m: `#define WBT_METADATA [0m[1;36m0xCCC8[0m[39m`[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis makes it clear that WBT_METADATA is no longer supported. However, this is [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moptional as leaving the constant defined but unused won't cause issues.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This is the Optimal Approach[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Complete elimination**: Removes all code paths that could trigger the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **No functionality loss**: The metadata feature is unused and undocumented - no [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlegitimate code depends on it[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Minimal risk**: Only removes dead code that serves no purpose[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Clean solution**: Removes global state and improves code quality[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Prevents similar attacks**: Eliminates the entire attack surface, not just one[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecific trigger[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Preserves Existing Logic[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Protocol compatibility**: Normal RFX encoding/decoding is unaffected as it [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnever uses WBT_METADATA[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **State machine**: The expectedDataBlockType flow remains unchanged for all [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlegitimate block types[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Test compatibility**: All existing tests pass as they don't use metadata [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblocks[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Encoder unchanged**: Encoder code is completely unaffected[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Other block types**: Processing of WBT_FRAME_BEGIN, WBT_REGION, WBT_EXTENSION,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWBT_FRAME_END remains identical[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses the Issues[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Fixes the crash**: Line [0m[1;36m734[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe crashing write[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is removed entirely[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Prevents attack vector**: Lines [0m[1;36m674[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m680[0m[39m that allow setting attacker-controlled[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maddresses are removed[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Prevents future attacks**: Even if an attacker crafts malicious FRAME_BEGIN or[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMETADATA blocks, they cannot be processed[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Improves security**: Removes global state that could be exploited across [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontext boundaries[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side Effect [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m**: WBT_METADATA blocks in input will now cause an error[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Mitigation**: This is desired behavior. These blocks are not part of legitimate[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRFX protocol usage in FreeRDP[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Impact**: Minimal - no legitimate encoders produce these blocks[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side Effect [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m**: Global variables are removed[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Mitigation**: [0m[3;35mNone[0m[39m needed - these variables were only used by the removed code[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Impact**: [0m[3;35mNone[0m[39m - no other code references these variables[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side Effect [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m**: Function signature changes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrfx_process_message_metadata [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremoved[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Mitigation**: [0m[3;35mNone[0m[39m needed - function is static and only called from one [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Impact**: [0m[3;35mNone[0m[39m - the call site is also removed[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe approach of removing unsupported/dangerous block type processing has precedent:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The `default` case in the switch statement [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1329[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1332[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m already rejects [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munknown block types[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Other block type handlers have strict validation and state checking[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The encoder only implements a subset of possible block types, showing selective [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msupport is normal[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Implementation Notes[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Order of removal**: Remove in the order specified to avoid breaking [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation at intermediate steps[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Line number shifts**: After removing lines [0m[1;36m142[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m143[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m179[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m180[0m[39m, subsequent [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline numbers will shift down[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Testing**: After the patch, fuzzing should not trigger the crash, and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlegitimate RFX codec usage should be unaffected[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Alternative to Step [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m**: If removing the constant from rfx_constants.h is [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproblematic [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., it's in a public header[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, it can be left defined but unused[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremoved code responsible for reading block offset and metadata data from the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstream. However, after applying the patch, the same type of crash persists at line [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m727[0m[39m of the same file, indicating that the patch did not resolve the underlying [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missue causing the segmentation fault.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer execution reveals multiple errors before the crash:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Three separate errors from the CLEAR codec regarding pixel index mismatches and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrun-length factor validation issues[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. A critical SEGV [0m[1;39m([0m[39msegmentation fault[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the RFX codec processing[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe crash details show:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Location**: `[0m[35m/src/FreeRDP/libfreerdp/codec/[0m[95mrfx.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m734:26[0m[39m` in [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rfx_process_message_metadata`[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Error Type**: AddressSanitizer detected a SEGV on an unknown address [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;36m0x7ff70ba70e20[0m[39m`[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Access Type**: WRITE memory access[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Scariness Score**: [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwild-addr-write[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe call stack indicates:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. `rfx_process_message_metadata` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m734[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. `rfx_process_message` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1320[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. `TestFreeRDPCodecRemoteFX` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m184[0m[1;39m)[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m460[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer was processing a test case through the TestFuzzCodecs harness, which [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered the vulnerability during RFX message processing.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch removes a conditional code block from `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.c` starting [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat line [0m[1;36m674[0m[39m. Specifically, the removed code:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m >= [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        UINT64 blockOffset = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, blockOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, metadataData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        metadataBlock += blockOffset;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis code was responsible for:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Checking if at least [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes remain in the stream[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Reading a [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit block offset value[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Reading a [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit metadata data value[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Adding the block offset to the metadataBlock pointer[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch completely removes this logic following the `numRegions` read operation.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Post-Patch Results[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the fuzzer execution shows:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The same three CLEAR codec errors persist [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexpected, as the patch targets RFX [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodec[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. A similar SEGV crash still occurs, but now at line [0m[1;36m727[0m[39m instead of line [0m[1;36m734[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The crash characteristics remain identical:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Same unknown address pattern [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m0x7fb9d82d8e20[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Same WRITE memory access type[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Same scariness score [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Same call stack pattern[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe call stack after patching:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. `rfx_process_message_metadata` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m727[0m[39m - moved up [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m lines due to code removal[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. `rfx_process_message` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1313[0m[39m - moved up [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m lines[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. `TestFreeRDPCodecRemoteFX` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m184[0m[39m - unchanged[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m460[0m[39m - unchanged[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe line numbers shifted by exactly [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m lines [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe number of lines removed[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrash still occurs in `rfx_process_message_metadata`, suggesting the root cause [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlies elsewhere in the function.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a holistic view of the issue, the following areas should be investigated:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **rfx_process_message_metadata function**: The complete implementation needs [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexamination, particularly:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Lines around [0m[1;36m727[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m734[0m[39m where the crash occurs[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Memory allocation and initialization of the `metadataBlock` pointer[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validation of stream data before dereferencing pointers[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **rfx_process_message function**: As the caller of [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rfx_process_message_metadata`, this function should be reviewed for:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Context initialization[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Memory allocation patterns[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Data validation before passing to metadata processing[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Stream handling**: The Stream operations need verification:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `Stream_GetRemainingLength` usage patterns[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `Stream_Read_*` functions and their boundary checks[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stream position and length management[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **metadataBlock pointer**: Investigation needed on:[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Where and how `metadataBlock` is allocated[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Its expected size and bounds[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How the index calculation at line [0m[1;36m727[0m[39m/[0m[1;36m734[0m[39m is performed[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Test input characteristics**: Understanding what makes this particular fuzzer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput trigger the crash:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The structure of the RFX message being processed[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Values of `frameIdx` and `numRegions`[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Overall message format and expected layout[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **CLEAR codec errors**: While not directly related to the crash, these errors [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurring before the SEGV might indicate broader data validation issues in the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodec layer.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
